description: Test specification file for the GameService in a Tic-Tac-Toe game project. It contains unit tests checking game initialization, move alternation, win detection, and reset functionality.

classes.name: GameService
classes.description: Service class managing game logic for Tic-Tac-Toe, including move handling, winner detection, and game state management.

methods.name: board
methods.description: Returns the current state of the game board as an array of cells.

methods.name: currentPlayer
methods.description: Returns the symbol of the player ('X' or 'O') to make the next move.

methods.name: winner
methods.description: Returns the symbol of the winning player if there's a winner, otherwise null.

methods.name: makeMove
methods.description: Executes a move at the given position on the board.

methods.name: reset
methods.description: Resets the game to its initial state.
